"NOT FOUND"|"quod ... teneretur: who assigns this reason? Note that obsidibus without ab is simply an ablative of means, not of agent."

"NOT FOUND"|"populi Romani hospitio atque amicitia: for almost three quarters of a century the Haedui had been allies and friends of the Roman people. Hospitium between two independent states denotes the relation of host and guest, requiring that each should extend to the other the rites of hospitality in the persons of their representatives and ambassadors; amicitia is a still stronger bond, requiring each state to adopt a friendly policy wherever the interests of the other are concerned; societas, a definite alliance, is the strongest bond that can exist between states."

