"ubi de eius adventu helvetii CERTIORES FACTI sunt, legatos ad eum mittunt nobilissimos civitatis, cuius legationis nammeius et verucloetius principem locum obtinebant, qui dicerent sibi esse in animo sine ullo maleficio iter per provinciam facere, propterea quod aliud iter haberent nullum: rogare ut eius voluntate id sibi facere liceat."|"12. certiores facti sunt: were informedlit. were made more certain. Observe that certiores is simply an adjective, agreeing with the subject Helvetiiqui dicerent: who were to say, or simply to say; volitive subjunctive in a relative clause of purpose; see qua . . . conveniant, p. 60, 1. 2; qui refers to nobilissimos."

