"NOT FOUND"|"Sibi persuaderi: that he was persuaded, lit. it was persuaded to him; eum ... repudiaturum is the subject of the impersonal persuaderi. Observe that persuadeo takes the dative in the passive as well as in the active, and that in the passive it is impersonal. Mi hi persuadet: he persuades me; mi hi persuadetur: I am persuaded."

