"NOT FOUND"|"Boios petentibus Haeduis . . . concessit: he granted the petition of the Haedui (lit. granted to the Haedui) that they might settle the Boii, etc. Here the construction is somewhat doubtful. Haeduis may be dative with concessit or in the ablative absolute, and ut . . . conlocarent may be the object either of petentibus or of concessit."

