"quin etiam, quod necessariam rem coactus caesari enuntiarit, INTELLEGERE SESE quanto id cum periculo fecerit, et ob eam causam quam diu potuerit tacuisse."|"8. Intellegere sese ... haberent: this long speech of the Gallic envoys is in the indirect discourse, depending on a verb of saying implied in gratulatum. We have already compared certain forms of indirect discourse with corresponding direct forms. It may now interest the student to see or to make more extended comparisons of direct and indirect forms. This speech of the Gallic envoys, if reported in the form of direct discourse, would read asfollows:Intellegimus, tametsi pro veteribus Helvetiorum iniuriis populi Romani ab his poenas bello repetisti, tamen eam rem non minus ex usu terrae Galliae quam populi Romani accidisse, propterea quod eo consilio florentissimis rebus domos suas Helvetii reliquerunt, uti toti Galliae bellum inferrent imperioque potirentur locumque domicilio ex magna copia deligerent, quem ex omni Gallia opportunissimum ac fructuosissimum iudicassent, reliquasque civitates stipendiarias haberent."

