"vulgo TOTIS CASTRIS testamenta obsignabantur."|"totis ... castris ... nudatis: as the whole camp was exposed; ablative absolute. It will be remembered that six legions were engaged in fortifying the camp when the attack began (p. 112,1. 24); two of these at once took their position on the left of the camp, two in front of it, and two on the right. Soon the two on the left, the 9th and the 10th (p. 115, 1. 25), routed the Atrebates and went in pursuit of them, while the nth and the 8th, who were stationed in front, went in pursuit of the Veromandui (p. 116, 1. 7). Thus the camp was exposed in front and on the left (a fronte et ab sinistra parte). At this juncture the whole force of the Nervii was led against the 12th and the 7th legions, who occupied a position on the right of the camp, and were, at the moment, its only defense; see plan in text, p. 113."

