"ipse diviciacum haeduum magnopere cohortatus docet QUANTO OPERE rei publicae communisque salutis intersit manus hostium distineri, ne cum tanta multitudine uno tempore confligendum sit."|"28. quanto opere . . . intersit: how much it concerns the republic and the common safety; an indirect question; quanto Opere, sometimes writtenCAESAR***S GALLIC WARquantopere, is in effect an adverb, but in its origin it is an ablative of difference. The subject of intersit is manus hostium distineri. For the case of rei publicae, see H. 449, 1; LM. 580; A. 222; G. 381; B. 211; (H. 408,1)."

