"NOT FOUND"|"citeriore Gallia = Cisalpina Gallia : i.e. Gaul south of the Alps, esset Caesar . . . demonstravimus: observe that Caesar, in speaking of himself as commander, regularly uses the third person, as esset Caesar; but that in speaking of himself as author he uses the first person, generally plural, as demonstravimus. H. 500, 2; A. 98, 1, b; B. 242, 3; (H. 446, n. 2). ita . . . demonstravimus: see p. 98,1. 5."

