"NOT FOUND"|"' Caesari . . . dandum: this sentence gives a list of the chief duties of a Roman commander on the eve of battle. Here notice that the several things to be done are all expressed by the periphrastic conjugation, and that the verb, esse, is expressed only with the first, erant agenda."

