"helvetii cum omnibus suis carris secuti impedimenta in unum locum contulerunt; ipsi confertissima acie, reiecto nostro equitatu, PHALANGE FACTA sub primam nostram aciem successerunt."|"phalange facta: the Macedonian phalanx, so celebrated in ancient warfare, was doubtless unknown to the Gauls. The Helvetic phalanx probably consisted simply of a body of soldiers in close array, under the cover of their shields close locked over their heads. This phalanx resembled the Roman testudo, as seen in plate VIII."

