"NOT FOUND"|"Celtae, Galli: predicate nominatives. Observe that the term Galli, like Gallia, is used in two senses. It usually denotes the inhabitants of Gaul as a whole, but it is often used, as in this instance, to designate the inhabitants of one division of the country, i.e. of Celtic Gaul. This distinction must be constantly borne in mind."

