"NOT FOUND"|"20. neque ... poterant: this is the principal or independent clause of the sentence. All that precedes is preparatory to it and grammatically dependent upon it, hut the independent clause is itself compound, consisting of three distinct clauses, introduced by neque ... neque ... neque, with the three subjects, subsidia, quid ... opus esset, and imperia."

