"NOT FOUND"|"omnes Belgas . . . has esse causas: this is an instance of the indirect discourse, oratio obliqua, very common in Caesar. It depends on certior fiebat, involving the idea of saying; see note on Caesarem certiorem faciunt\ p. 63, 1. 17. In the direct discourse this passage would stand thus:Omnes Belgae, quam tertiam esse Galliae partem diximus, contra populum Romanum coniurant obsidesque inter se dant. Coniurandi hae sunt causae."

