"NOT FOUND"|"absunt, est: the mood shows that these clauses are not a part of the report, but Caesar***s own statements."

"NOT FOUND"|"pueri, senes, mulieresque: subject of exissent, to be supplied from exisset above. On the use of que in mulieresque, observe that between three or more coordinate words the conjunction is, in general, either repeated or omitted altogether; but that que may be used with the last member of a series even when the conjunction is omitted between the other words, as in this instance."

