"NOT FOUND"|"30. Haec ... . contexebantur: these were connected by timbers placed in the direction of the length of the bridge. This was a trestle bridge. Caesar, having now described one trestle, supporting one section of the bridge, leaves us to infer that all the trestles were constructed in the same way. He nowOriginal from***UNIVERSITY OF IOWACAESAR***S GALLIC WARproceeds to show how these trestles were connected, and how the bridge was covered."

