"NOT FOUND"|"cur . . . iudicaret: what kind -of a subjunctive would this be in the direct discourse? H. 559, 4; LM. 723; A. 268; G. 466; B. 277; (H. 484, 5)."

"SI QUOs adversum proelium et fuga gallorum commoveret, hos, si quaererent, reperire posse diuturnitate belli defatigatis gallis ariovistum, cum multos menses castris se ac paludibus tenuisset neque sui potestatem fecisset, desperantes iam de pugna et dispersos subito adortum magis ratione et consilio quam virtute vicisse."|"si quo .. . esset: render freely, if they should be needed anywhere; indirect clause, depending on ut. .. possent. H. 652; LM. 793; A. 342; G. 663, 1; B.324; (H. 529, II)."

"NOT FOUND"|"qui: note that qui agrees with Rheno, not with flumine, and also that qui in line 12 agrees with Rhodano."

"NOT FOUND"|"cum ... divideret: causal clause; subjunctive in the direct discourse."

"NOT FOUND"|"quarum : partitive genitive, depending on unam = unam partem. H. 442; LM. 560; A. 216, a; G. 367; B. 201; (H. 397)."

"volusenus perspectis regionibus omnibus QUANTUM EI facultatis dari potuit, qui navi egredi ac se barbaris committere non auderet, v. die ad caesarem revertitur quaeque ibi perspexisset renuntiat."|"quantum ei facultatis: as far as the opportunity, etc."

