"NOT FOUND"|"castris: place and means; cf. oppidis recipere, p. 101,1. 8."

"helvetii ea spe deiecti navibus iunctis ratibusque compluribus factis, alii vadis rhodani, qua minima altitudo fluminis erat, non numQUAM INterdiu, saepius noctu, si perrumpere possent conati, operis munitione et militum concursu et telis repulsi, hoc conatu destiterunt."|"Quam in partem: to whatever place,quaeque signa: and whatever standards,ad haec constitit: near these (i.e. these standards) he took his place."

"NOT FOUND"|"Quod: this, i.e. the mode of attack just described, turn: on this occasion."

"NOT FOUND"|"CUl. . . fidem habebat: in whom he was wont to place the fullest confidence in everything; lit. in reference to whom he was having the highest confidence of all things; cui is dative of reference; rerum limits fidem and adds emphasis to summam."

"nam quod hostibus adpropinquabat, consuetudine sua caesar vi LEGIONES EXPEDITAS ducebat;  post eas totius exercitus impedimenta conlocarat; inde duae legiones quae proxime conscriptae erant totum agmen claudebant praesidioque impedimentis erant."|"legiones expeditas ducebat: see 70."

"caesar id quod erat suspicatus aliquid novi a barbaris initum consilii, cohortes quae in statione erant secum in eam partem proficisci, EX RELIQUIS duas in stationem succedere, reliquas armari et confestim sese subsequi iussit."|"ex reliquis .. . succedere: two of the other (six) cohorts to take their place on guard. He could spare only two cohorts to guard the gates."

"NOT FOUND"|"2 3- diligentia: not diligence, but care, watchfulness."

